content: I like the original game and so disappointed with this remake, the performance is really bad
The touch UI at the main hub is a bit uncomfortable. So far I think the game is ok. For people considering to buy this game I recommend playing Deemo first.

Thanks for releasing Deemo Reborn on android. If possible, can you please add controller support for this game? I have a bluetooth controller with me and I really want to play this game with what I have. Thanks in advance

I love it ‚ô•Ô∏è Ok ...( Edit ) : to the developers, This game urgently need a new game plus mode and frame drop fix (my processor is sd 845) ! ... This game is unique in which it is half songs and half from easy to head rolling puzzles. It require strong device to run 3d smoothly, the game is ultimately fun for those who love puzzle to music type of games What i liked:the graphic , the atmosphere and the reshape of the old game. What i didnt like: some lags , no game+ mode, fiew songs

A bad port of a good game, the touch ui is awkward and clunky and unfortunately in rhythm mode it's almost unplayable by the way it's reactions to touch is, it's quite disappointing. Personally I think they should kept having 6 rows like it does for keyboard/controller and had each row act as a "button" kinda like malodys 4k mode works. Also the inclusion of keyboard and controller inputs would be nice.
Thanks for the update, now we just need optimization
Bought the app but it was overall so buggy. hope they fix it soon. i always have a problem running it even though i have a flagship phone it fails almost all the time. sigh...
I Like It
love this game

loved deemo, not sure how to feel about -Reborn-, sometimes the game is unplayable with all the stutters from the sliders and whatnot. I still purchased all the packs tho, i hope i'll be able to play them one day stutter free

I love deemo original. I enjoy the game but too bad doesn't have some things from the original version Deemo with Alice room and so on. But I'll still continue playing as it's lovely everytime I play.
grant game but for some reason i cant buy the games dlc i just really like the songs in the dlc is all...but cant buy T^T
This rhythm game is good to play. Is very addictive, especially all rayark games. Im always look forward for new games to come up. I love it.

I don't know why people is giving this game bad rating. This game is awesome if you use better device (in my case is Poco X3). I think deemo reborn is fantastic and im still wait for deemo II. After all, if i can give rating this game is 11/10, above my expectation :)
FPS drop‚òπ
Blurry textures, stiff animations, bad fps performance. I totally regret buying the mobile version, It's like a cheap port. Shoulda known about it and stick to the pc version
Please increase the calibration it's very limited and can't enjoy the game that much Edit: They added audio calibration, thanks rayark
It will be better if there is 60 fps option
4 star for now, the gameplay is fun, just like original deemo, but you need improve the control when exploring the room, it's rather sluggish and slow, but overall is good
The original is better.

This is just the normal version of Deemo but inferior in every way. The esthetic of the game, the interface, the design... Everything feels like a draft. It's a good game nonetheless but better to invest on the actual Deemo game, it's a lot more enjoyable and worth the time.
Can't even go into game and it keeps crushed.

The game is beautiful but they need better calibration options for the game! It makes the game a little unplayable... I'm not getting a refund because I love Deemo and want to support Rayark but if you don't love Deemo I suggest not spending the money till they update the game and fix it.

While this a solid 4/5 game but, the amount of performance bugs for example the fps drops while doing slide notes making some songs harder to do (EDIT Turn Off Vibration in the game that is the cause of fps drops).

I've seen many videos of the game and I'm a big fan of Rayark's games, but I've immediately refunded this one because it's not opening at all. When I'm trying to open it, it just crashes and takes me to the home screen. I'll look up for this problem to get fixed.
Time to sail from where i've left from... Nice bug, AC with AutoPlay consider as Achievement Unlocked.
Played on Steam and it's very good. But on mobile there's a lot of bugs. Been playing Cytus,Cytus2,Deemo and all great! Don't let me down for this mobile version.

Gameplay is not smooth even with a Kirin 990. I look forward to more updates which will hopefully be a lot more optimised. Calibration does not seem to work. +0.050 and -0.050 both feel the same. Please fix!
The game isnt ported over properly, the controls are super clunky and note visual timings are weird

The overall game was very beautiful, touching and fun. However, it need a higher end device to play, if not in some part it will get stuck or jam. The controller in game need to be polished . Even thought I'd play Deemo (original) before years ago, but I think Reborn are also worth to play even though the storyline are the same. Also, there's one more things that I felt disappointed for this game is: I didn't get to see Deemo's (H**s) face at the end of the story in this version!!!
I really love this game. Deemo was the reason i start to learn piano 6 years ago. Beautiful song and story makes this game excellent.

Honestly the move from 2D to 3D was a massive downgrade. Additionally expect the game to run at very low frames even on a high end phone. Movement feels awful, like you are sliding on ice. Skip this one.

After seeing the review i still purchase the game because i am a big fan for deemo. But right after i install it, i realise the problem is really serious. The sensitivity of the key are weird, at first i thought i was my mistake but soon i realise it is not. This issue is really serious for a music game~ I hope that the improvement can be done as soon as possible.

I see potential for lots of improvements. It lags a lot on phones (and my phone is already considered "new" coming out just last year) Maybe it will be difficult to fix it, maybe it won't. For now it's not living up to the cost(Cytus II is smoother) if the lag issues are fixed, I will play it again

An excellent game. Currently have almost all of Rayark's rhythm games. The problem with this one is that there is no option to change the audio offset. The chart hits before the sound. Calibration just adjust the touch timings but that isn't enough even if I max or out. Using Galaxy Tab S7

Huge fan of og Deemo. I have Reborn on Steam and decided to buy it again for Android bc I love you guys. It's buggy in loading screens and some times the screen stays black and doesn't load unless i close and restart app. Hope it gets updated soon!
The game is very good but the problem is, this game is a little bit laggy and I think it is just 30fps, I hope you could put a 60fps feature in the settings. <3

I love the game even the story,song and the graphics... one problem is the notes because sometimes its deley...but im using mi 10t for me i love it i wish for the next update i want to fix that problem and thanks i will appreciate this game and i will rate this 10/10 stars.

Can't load file. Im using samsung galaxy A50 Downloaded the game yesterday, played pretty fine, just a little lag and delay on button. But today when i tried to load the file, the game keep crashing. App immediately closed and back to homescreen. I hope this can be fixed, because im not planning to change device anytime soon.
It's a masterpiece, good game üòÅ
Great graphic üëç

Performance is capped at default, although using a high end phone, Xiaomi 10T Pro. Other Rayark games can run 144Hz, which is okay. Please add more adjustment options which helps utilize usage of processing on high end mobile devices for a richer experience, as on PC steam, game is doing much smoother, where I can even play the game in 144Hz. Other than that, character controls are simulated like gamepad control, a bit uncomfortable. UI looked a bit small from my view, probably due to resolution

I have purchased this game on PS4, Steam, and now on Android. Deemo reborn is one of the best games ever made and I highly recommend it to anybody that wants to experience a beautiful and heartwarming story.

Instabuy but i found out that it was poorly optimized. It has very low fps even in SD865 device. Deemo 1 feels better than this, but i hope this one gets updated soon for smoother and better gaming experience.

Cool concepts but a few Major problems add more customisation features and the ability ot run the game at 120 and 144hz and add more specific graphics options other than low and default There is one huge issue and that is with lag everything seems slow and hard to use despite me using a note 20 ultra i can run genshin impact at max settings but can't play this. It needs some serious software optimisations since as of now its so buggy and and laggy that it's unplayable.
It's ok, but the performance can be better
Needs heavy optimization. Gameplay stutters even on low quality. Camera controls, for lack of a better word, suck. Needs more refinement for QOL improvements to make the puzzle mechanics more fluid.
Overall the game is great, but I experience a low fps during the gameplay. Hope this can be fixed

I'm a Fan of rhythm games specially the deemo and cytus. and playing it is not waste at all. since this game just launch. bugs occur. but theirs at least 2 problems in my perspective. 1st i that this game are built for phone above average to play. i wish theirs an even lower graphics besides "low". 2nd is the difficulty. since its originally created for ps4 (if im right). the difficulty is slightly easier that the challenge remove. Great game but please improve more. and still waiting on Deemo2
Tried playing, the game doesn't work well. Can't go past 20 fps and overheated my device. Not too much to say, I'll go for the simple version.
Woo hoo, it's been 5 years i think since i played deemo
I think there is some bugs now but overall a good experience. Im using a Samsung s9+ and the screen freezes after a song is done.
Its so good, but my phone can't handle it so i am so sorry that i refunded it

Great port! This game sure favours flagship device specs and it's running great (not that perfect) on my galaxy S9+ with just some few bugs especially the freezing loading screens after finishing a song, but overall it's worth the wait!

The graphic and lags is still acceptable but during the game, I always felt some lags or delays when pressing the notes and sometimes when I click a note it went to the notes behind the notes which is so frustrating.

I've gotta say, I'm very disappointed. The game got super ugly on its way from PC to mobile. I understand they had to downgrade the graphics, but they brought them down so much and it barely helped the FPS. Now the piano looks like a sponge, the play area is desolate, and the song selection screen is gross. I'll stick with PC, thanks.
Crash my whole Device took forever to load content despite me having unlimited high speed data. Didn't even get a chance to play.
I already purchased this on steam and i love how puzzles works there OwO. But i already unins because lag )): Hope it won't lag on Galaxy S10+

Deemo is my favourite game ever, I played first game more than 300hours and sometimes still playing with 8.5speed in hard haha but sadly I have some calibration mistake in this game. I hope it's cause of my phone or i wish you can fix it as soon as possible cause i wanna play this perfect game as perfect as i can. Btw I'm waiting for " pure white " and " Oceanus " :3
Great game! PS4 version was a blast, so I thought I'd pick it up on Mobile as well!
